Package org.lfj.lang.op

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayAccessor
    This is like an aload instruction except it is also a place form.
    ArrayLength
    This the array length instruction of the java virtual machine instruction set.
    BranchProcedure
    This is equivalent to a goto instruction in the instruction set.
    Constructor
    This is a generalization of constructor functions in the java virtual machine.
    DefinedApplicative
    These are the applicatives which are defined by programs in the java virtual machine rather then ones that are defined by the java virtual machine instruction set itself.
    FieldAccessor
    This is equivalent to a getfield instruction except it is also a place form.
    IncrementationProcedure
    This is the iinc operation in the instruction set.
    LogicalFunction
    A generalization of the logical functions of the java virtual machine.
    MathematicalFunction
    A class of functions that deal with all the mathematical functions defined by the java virtual machine including all arithmetic, logic, and cast operations.
    ModificationProcedure
    This sets some place form to some value which is passed as an argument.
    ObjectFunction
    An object function requires a type argument to its instruction definition, then it puts its arguments onto the stack in order to operate on them.
    PrimitiveFunction
    A class of functions returns primitive values on the stack.
    Procedure
    A class of applicatives that do not return anything onto the stack.
    StandardProcedure
    This is a container class for miscellaneous procedures of the java virtual machine which are not defined elsewhere.
    SwitchProcedure
    This procedure deals with branching to different locations based upon some table.
